title: Game of the Week: Bishop Gorman hosts N.J. powerhouse
text: Share Updated: 10/23 7:45 pm L AS VEGAS (KSNV News3LV) – Operation Football’s Game of the Week is Don Bosco at Bishop Gorman High School.Don Bosco of New Jersey is Bishop Gorman’s final out-of-state opponent for the season.Should the undefeated Gaels win, they'll likely secure the mythical national championship for the second straight year.Don Bosco is 4-2 this season.Bishop Gorman head coach Kenny Sanchez warned that record is misleading since Don Bosco's schedule was ranked the toughest in the country.Bishop Gorman star wide receiver Tyjon Lindsey said the team is well aware how tough Friday night might be.“They're a smack in the mouth team,” said Lindsey. “If we win this one, this would be a big one. They're very competitive, and they won't give a win to anybody. I know that for a fact.”
